<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-450-576  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 450 576.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  May 14 1990 v12 n20 p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technology that can transcend borders will win in the future.andO;(Connections) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buerger, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The emergence of 'stateless' corporations or multinationalorganizations that operate in various countries bring with it theneed for information processing technology that transcends asingle language.andP;  These corporations also require rapid andefficient information sharing all over the globe.andP;  To support theinformation needs of these multinational conglomerates, networkshave to evolve into internetworks that build in native-languagesupport and naming services capable of language translation.andO;Among the significant products that address multinationalrequirements are: 3Com's 3+Open Kanji LAN Manager, Banyan Systems'Vines 4.0 network operating system and Street Talk.andP;  Theseproducts provide native-mode network support for foreign languagesand create a mixed-language environment accessible viainternational X.25 links.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Multinational CorporationInternationalNetworksLanguage TranslationInformation ProcessingFuture of Computing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>